com.github.rolecraftdev.guild

Class Guild

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.rolecraftdev.guild.Guild

  • public final class Guild
extends Object
    Represents a Guild in Rolecraft. Guilds are player-creatable and provide lots of functionality.

      • getPlayerRanks

        public Set<GuildRank> getPlayerRanks(UUID player)
        Get a Set of all of the GuildRanks the given player has within this Guild. Note that this method will return null if the specified player has no GuildRanks in this Guild.
        Parameters:
        player - - The player to get the GuildRanks within this Guild for
        Returns:
        A Set of ranks the player has in this Guild, or null if no GuildRanks are found

      • getInfluence

        public int getInfluence()
        Get the current influence of this Guild without calculating the up-to-date value. If the real influence value is required, use calculateInfluence() instead.
        Returns:
        The Guild's last calculated influence value
        See Also:
        calculateInfluence()

      • calculateInfluence

        public int calculateInfluence()
        Calculates and returns the most up-to-date influence value for this Guild, based on the influence values of this Guild's members combined. If an estimate value is also fine, utilise getInfluence(), for performance reasons.
        Returns:
        The up-to-date influence value for this Guild
        See Also:
        getInfluence()

      • getName

        public String getName()
        Get the name of this Guild, which should be unique. Despite the fact that guild names should be unique, they can change, and thus should not be used for comparisons of guilds. For correct equivalence checks, simply use the overridden equals(Object) method.
        Returns:
        Its unique name
        See Also:
        equals(Object)

      • setLeader

        public void setLeader(UUID leader)

        leader - - The unique identifier of the new leader
